        // For each a[i] (0 <= i < n-1), we want a[i] + b[i] to be a multiple of n.
        // We choose b[i] such that a[i] + b[i] = k*n.
        // Specifically, we want a[i] + b[i] = (a[i] % n == 0 ? 0 : n - (a[i] % n)) * n. No, this is wrong.
        // We want a[i] + b[i] to be 0 mod n.
        // Let current_val = a[i]. We want current_val + b[i] = 0 (mod n).
