    //   So, if we can construct a partition where:
    //   (1) `elements[0]` and `elements[1]` are in the same group (to get `S_min` as min_f).
    //   (2) `elements[n-1]` and `elements[n-2]` are in different groups (to get `S_max + h` as max_f).
    //   Then the goodness would be `(S_max + h) - S_min`.

    //   Can we achieve this?
    //   Partition:
    //   Group 1: `elements[0]`, `elements[1]`, ..., `elements[n-2]`
    //   Group 2: `elements[n-1]`
    //   (This requires n >= 2. If n=2, elements[0] in G1, elements[1] in G2. Then S_min is not in G1.
    //    If n=2, elements[0] in G1, elements[1] in G2. min_f = elements[0]+elements[1]+h. max_f = elements[0]+elements[1]+h. Goodness = 0.
